This paper presents a randomized data structure for dynamic graph connectivity, which involves algorithms for maintaining connectivity information in a changing graph. This topic falls under the area of data structures and algorithms, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and graph theory, which are relevant to cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.CG (computational geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses applications to network engineering (cs.NE) and system implementation (cs.SI).
